lavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Ostensibly from the vocabulary word denoting the flower (Latin <i>rosa</i>). However, the name was in use throughout the Middle Ages, long before any of the other girls' names derived from flowers, which are generally of 19th-century origin. In part it may refer to the flower as a symbol of the Virgin Mary, but it seems more likely that it also has a Germanic origin, probably as a short form of various girls' names based on <i>hros</i> ‘horse’ or <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’. The Latinate form <i>Rohesia</i> is commonly found in documents of the Middle Ages. As well as being a name in its own right, it is currently used as a short form of   Rosemary   and, less often (because of their different pronunciation), of other names beginning <i>Ros-</i>, such as   Rosalind   and   Rosamund ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Rose DE SALMAND was born in 1250, in Ariano Irpino, Avellino, Campania, Italy. She married Gaucelin Ier DE BARJAC in 1290. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 19 October 1329, at the age of 79."},"et":{"1250–19 octobre 1329":"1250–19. oktoober 1329","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1240–1311":"1240–1311","1294–1353":"1294–1353","1270–1354":"1270–1354","1250–1329":"1250–1329","19 octobre 1329":"19. oktoober 1329","1311":"1311","1354":"1354","1353":"1353","environ 1270":"umbes 1270","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1294":"1294","1293":"1293","1270":"1270","1329":"1329","1290":"1290","Ariano Irpino, Avellino, Campania, Italy":"Ariano Irpino, Avellino, Campania, Itaalia","Bourg-Saint-Andéol, Ardèche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, France":"Bourg-Saint-Andéol, Ardèche, Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1250–19 octobre 1329":"1250–19. lokakuuta 1329","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1240–1311":"1240–1311","1294–1353":"1294–1353","1270–1354":"1270–1354","1250–1329":"1250–1329","19 octobre 1329":"19. lokakuuta 1329","1311":"1311","1354":"1354","1353":"1353","environ 1270":"noin 1270","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1294":"1294"